Cervical intraepithelial neoplasia: an attempt to propose rules for good medical practice. The authors emphasize the advantages of the term "cervical intraepithelial neoplasia" (CIN) over "dysplasia" and "carcinoma-in-situ". The rules for good medical practice in treating CIN are based on several starting points, namely: proven role of the human papillomavirus (HPV) in the development of CIN current possibilities to diagnose and to prevent HPV infections